<TITLE> Land phone shift charge cut </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 25 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Limited has cut the charge for shifting land phone to Tk 500 for Dhaka and Tk 300 for other areas, it announced on Thursday. The BTCL also decided to cut charge for changing address, connection fee of Wireless Local Loop or WLL, and charge of Integrated Services Digital Network or ISDN. The new rates will be effective from Oct 1, a press statement said. The BTCL has also planned to launch toll free numbers which will start with 0800, the release said. The decisions were taken at a meeting of the board of directors of the state-run company. The previous charge for shifting land phone was Tk 1000 for Dhaka and Chittagong and Tk 500 for the rest of the country. Fee for changing address has been cut to Tk 500 from Tk 1,000 for Dhaka, Tk 300 from Tk 1,000 for Chittagong, Tk 300 from Tk 500 for district towns and Tk 100 from Tk 300 for upazilas. WLL connection fee has been cut to Tk 1,500 from Tk 5,100 and ISDN charge to Tk 15,920 from Tk 30,000. bd
